Title: Object instance recognition using best increasing subsequence
Source title: Proceedings - 11th 2016 International Conference on Knowledge, Information and Creativity Support Systems, KICSS 2016
Affiliations: Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: David Harjono, K., Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia; Kusuma, G.P., Computer Science, Bina Nusantara University, Jakarta, Indonesia
Abstract: Object instance recognition enables the realization of many potential applications, such as information retrieval, scene understanding and human computer interaction. However, it is still a challenging problem in computer vision. The appearance of an object is affected by variations in illumination, viewpoint and occlusion. In this contribution, we propose an object instance recognition method based on Best Increasing Subsequence. It estimates a set of geometrically consistent feature pairs and at the same time, maximizes the total similarity score between test and train images. Our experimental results show that the proposed method outperforms the existing geometric verification methods, RANSAC Homography and Weighted LIS. © 2016 IEEE.
Index Keywords: Geometric verifications; Homographies; Recognition methods; Scene understanding; Similarity scores; Human computer interaction
